  "title": "FULL TIME STUDENT CARE JUNIOR TRAINER",
  "description": "<p><strong>FULL-TIME STUDENT CARE JUNIOR TRAINER</strong><br />Hougang Ave 1 & 5 | $1,450–$1,570/month | Mon – Fri 6 hours<br />Work with kids, short hours, training provided!</p><p>Looking for a rewarding part-time/full-time job working with children?<br />Whether you’re a student, young parent, career-break professional, or mature applicant, we welcome anyone who is energetic, committed, and enjoys guiding children.</p><p><strong>Pay & Progression</strong></p><ul><li>3 days paid training at $11/hr</li><li>3-month probation after training: $1,450/month</li><li>Post-probation pay: $1,570/month</li><li>1-year commitment → eligible for performance assessment</li><li>Reviews commitment, consistency, reliability, and performance</li><li>Rewards / incentives given subject to assessment</li></ul><p>Short hours, structured training, and clear growth — we value your commitment and effort!</p><p><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p><ul><li>Pick up students from school</li><li>Oversee meal times</li><li>Supervise homework, revision and activity</li><li>Communicate with parents via app</li><li>Provide guidance & discipline</li></ul><p>This is student care supervision — no formal teaching required.</p><p><strong>Working Hours</strong></p><ul><li>12:15pm – 6:15pm (30 minutes break)</li><li>5 days/week</li></ul><p>Short hours: Perfect for those balancing family, study, or other commitments</p><p><strong>Who Can Apply</strong></p><ul><li>O-Level / Diploma holders (local/private)</li><li>Young parents or caregivers seeking short hours</li><li>Career-break professionals or mature applicants (energetic and fit for an active environment)</li><li>Anyone looking for a structured, rewarding, full-time role</li></ul><p><strong>How to Apply</strong><br />WhatsApp 9489 3552 with:</p><ul><li>Name</li><li>Age</li><li>Gender</li><li>Race</li><li>Languages spoken</li><li>Languages written</li><li>Highest Qualification</li><li>School course (if studying)</li><li>Graduation date (if studying)</li><li>PSLE score</li><li>Commitment period</li></ul><p>PRs & candidates with valid work passes welcome.</p><p>Work with children, gain experience, enjoy short hours, and get rewarded for your commitment!</p>",
